## `packages/registry`

Source of truth for what the CLI installs. **No install logic outside registry metadata.**

```
packages/registry/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts
│   ├── registry.types.ts
│   ├── validate-registry.ts
│   ├── validate-registry-item.ts
│   ├── items/            # One file per installable item (metadata)
│   ├── styles/           # Registry style entries (e.g. theme.ts)
│   └── utilities/        # Shared utility metadata (e.g. cn.ts)
├── templates/
│   ├── primitives/<Name>/   # Primitive install templates
│   ├── blocks/<Name>/       # Block install templates
│   ├── templates/<Name>/    # Template install templates
│   ├── shared/utils/        # e.g. cn.ts
│   └── styles/              # tokens.css, theme.css templates
├── scripts/
│   ├── sync-component-templates.mjs   # Sync ui primitives → templates
│   ├── sync-block-templates.mjs       # Sync ui blocks/templates → templates
│   ├── sync-all-templates.mjs         # Run both sync scripts
│   ├── check-registry-styles-sync.mjs # Verify style templates vs token output
│   ├── lib/registry-styles-sync.mjs   # Shared compare helpers for style sync
│   └── registry-item-generator.mjs
├── vitest.config.ts
└── test/
    ├── validate-registry.test.ts
    └── registry-styles-sync.test.ts
```

**Exports:** `.`, `./templates/*` (templates ship with the package).

Every registry item must declare: files, dependencies, utilities, styles, target paths.

